# Eval Harness Standards

When changing the agent harness:

- Every new policy must emit `AgentTraceEvent` records.
- Every new policy must include at least one deterministic or heuristic scorer.
- Never treat LLM judge scores as the only success criterion.
- All terminal commands must pass through a command safety classifier.
- Any retry policy must define `max_attempts` and a loop-break condition.
- Every blocked command or blocked file access must appear in the trace.
- Every final answer must be grounded in actual diff and test-result data.
- Prefer small, inspectable policy objects over hidden prompt-only behavior.
- Keep fixture traces deterministic and reviewable.

Before submitting changes, run:

```bash
pnpm validate:fixtures
pnpm eval:baseline
pnpm eval
```
